Happy Monday! This week is all about recognizing a very special class and very special people beginning with the WLB Class of 2020. They will finish up their WLB careers this week and get ready to take on LCHS! We are very proud of each and every one of them! Three to four graduate profiles will be posted daily. Stay tuned all week!

It has been a great journey watching them grow into young women and men. It would be impossible to name every single accomplishment achieved by this class over their years at WLB as there are so many, but the hope is to highlight some of them this week! Good luck and congratulations to the Class of 2020.

post_text:
Tomorrow is May 1st. This is the date that begins the ‚Äúcountdown‚Äù to the end of the year (at WLB...it is called the Crazy Days of May). This time is usually spent with themed days, recognition banquets/assemblies, Honors Day, lots of fun, Field Day, and graduation. This year is a bit different, but we are determined to recognize our students and graduates for all of their hard work and accomplishments. There is no doubt in the minds of every single person at WLB that we will come out of this time together and even STRONGER!!!

Virtual Honors Day will be May 21st via the WLB Facebook page.

Graduation has been postponed to June 19th at 7:00 p.m. if possible. However, the graduating class of 2020 will also be honored via the WLB Facebook page on their planned graduation date of May 22nd at 7:00 p.m. as well.

Thank you so much WLB families! This has been a hard transition, but we are doing great things together! It is not easy, but times that challenge us truly make us stronger!

Governor Pritzker announced the extension of the stay at home order today. This means schools will not reopen as planned. The order extends through April 30th. WLB will proceed as planned with packet/material delivery next Thursday, April 9th beginning around 10:00 a.m. via bus routes. This will be a porch/mailbox delivery. All precautions will be taken to deliver safely.
Please continue to check e-mail for updates. SchoolReach messages will also deliver information.
WLB faculty and staff truly miss our students. Our hearts break a little more each day we are not physically in school. We will continue to do our best to connect in other ways. Do the best that you can during this time. Spend time with your family while at home and take care of yourselves! üíôüíöüíôüíöüíôüíöüíôüíö

post_text:
Governor Pritzker just announced a ‚Äúshelter in place‚Äù order beginning tomorrow (Saturday) at 5:00 pm. Along with this order, he announced the new school resume date as April 8th. WLB is on spring break that week. WLB will resume on April 13th.

Teachers will be sending updated learning opportunities for the few days between the original resume date and spring break. These are learning opportunities for your children while they are at home. These are not graded assignments that are mandatory. We are just offering some type of continuity of learning as best we can at this point. Do not stress about getting everything accomplished. Many teachers are offering Zoom meetings to connect with their classes. Please keep an eye out for those schedules.

Meals will continue to be provided Monday to Friday. Please reach out to me if your family needs anything. I will do my best to provide what is needed for your family.

We will get through this time. I will keep everyone updated to the best of my ability.

Mrs. B

WLB Community: Governor Pritzker issued a directive to close Illinois schools beginning on Tuesday, March 17th. School will be in session on Monday, March 16th with doors opening at normal time at 7:50 a.m. and will dismiss at 3:10 p.m. E-Learning packets/instructions will be given to students on Monday. The March 30th date is fluid as the situation will be monitored and reassessed to determine if schools will reopen or the ‚Äúshutdown‚Äù period will be extended.
This is an unprecedented event. Thank you for your understanding and patience as all districts in Illinois navigate through this directive.

post_text:
Today was a great day for the WLB community! The Hoops for Heroes fundraiser for the Land of Lincoln Honor Flight was a HUGE success! I cannot thank the sponsors, volunteers, students, and community enough for their generosity! We raised enough to send a minimum of 10 veterans on the Honor Flight! I am truly thankful for the willingness to come together to support this great cause! Our hope is to make this an annual event!
#proudtobeawolverine

post_text:
Due to inclement weather in the area, PTO Skate night has been cancelled. The boys 7th grade sectional game in Champaign has been rescheduled to tomorrow (Thursday) at 5:30 pm. when weather conditions improve. The 8th grade Regional Championship game scheduled for tomorrow evening has been postponed to Monday evening at 6:00 pm. The volleyball game scheduled for Decatur this evening has also been cancelled.

Due to potential inclement weather during the morning hours and food service, WLB will utilize an Alternative Learning Day tomorrow along with other local districts. Students will bring home instructions for an ALD. Teachers will be available from 8:00-3:00 via e-mail and/or Google Classroom.

Thank you for your flexibility and understanding as we navigate through the winter months and try new ways of learning.

Stay safe and warm!

WLB will dismiss at 1:30 today due to the predicted snow, wind, and freezing rain showing on the current radar. This time will allow us to maximize the school day while being able to deliver students home safely before the freezing rain is scheduled to begin. Staff will also be able to travel home safely.

Volleyball game and all practices this evening have been cancelled.

Stay warm and safe!
